<seg id="229">5.1 Intra-Community Transactions</seg>
<seg id="230">The following diagram illustrates the process of processing information by the tax administrations of the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic during the intra-Community supply and acquisition of goods.</seg>
<seg id="231">5.1.1 Intra-Community Delivery</seg>
<seg id="232">If the VAT payer carries out an intra-Community supply, he is obliged to submit an SH by the 25th day after the end of the calendar quarter.</seg>
<seg id="233">The payer in the Czech Republic provides in the SH summary information about his supplies of goods to another EU Member State exempt from VAT for the previous calendar quarter.</seg>
<seg id="234">The payer in the Slovak Republic is obliged to enter in the SH the value of goods that have been exempted and delivered from the Czech Republic to other EU Member States during the calendar quarter period.</seg>
<seg id="235">Data on the value of the goods delivered are always presented in SH in Czech and Slovak currencies, broken down by individual tax entities, with an indication of their VAT number, under which they were registered in their country.</seg>
<seg id="236">Data on services are not included in the SH.</seg>
<seg id="237">If the payer in the Czech Republic finds that he has given incorrect data in the SH, he is obliged to submit a subsequent SH.</seg>
<seg id="238">If the payer in SR finds that the information given in the SH was incomplete or incorrect, he will file a corrective SH before the deadline for submission of the SH, after which he is obliged to file an additional SH.</seg>
<seg id="239">The VIES system allows for the exchange of information on the registration data of VAT registered payers in EU Member States.</seg>
<seg id="240">Payers from the Czech Republic or the Slovak Republic can check whether the VAT number of the relevant customer is registered in the EU Member State.</seg>
<seg id="241">The data from the submitted SH are grouped on MF CLO and DR CLO by VIES according to the individual VAT numbers of the purchasers.</seg>
<seg id="242">The aggregate value of all deliveries for each customer's VAT number and the code of the method of fulfilment from all its Czech and Slovak suppliers, the so-called L1QD files, will be created.</seg>
<seg id="243">Data from the L1QD files shall be sent to the relevant EU Member States no later than three months after the end of the quarter to which the data relate.</seg>
