<seg id="278">5.1.2 Intra-Community acquisition</seg>
<seg id="279">The VIES system provides, inter alia, information on the values of intra-community transactions within EU Member States.</seg>
<seg id="280">Acquisition of goods in the Czech Republic</seg>
<seg id="281">In the Czech Republic, data received from SH submitted by payers from other EU Member States (delivered by L1QD) are processed by MF CLO.</seg>
<seg id="282">During processing, the data are converted at the minimum and maximum daily exchange rates of the Czech National Bank for the relevant period and then compared with the value of the acquisition indicated by Czech payers in the DAP for the relevant quarter.</seg>
<seg id="283">The value of acquisitions of goods reported by payers in the DAP should be in the range of the minimum and maximum converted value of L1QD (L1min and L1max).</seg>
<seg id="284">If the value reported in the DAP is less than L1min, a "verification order" is generated for the payer with the most significant irregularities.</seg>
<seg id="285">Orders to verify the acquisition of goods are a warning to problematic tax entities and are passed on to the local tax authorities, which must investigate the data transmitted.</seg>
