<seg id="203">6. Management of state funds and assets</seg>
<seg id="204">6.1 Economic analysis</seg>
<seg id="205">In the Czech Republic, in 2001, the approved budgeted expenditure of SUZ was increased by CZK 103,077,000 by 13 budget measures.</seg>
<seg id="206">Of these, 89,979,000 CZK (87.29%) were earmarked funds. Most of it was intended to deal with the consequences of the Kosovo crisis (44,538,000 CZK) and to provide health care to asylum seekers (38,870,000 CZK).</seg>
