<seg id="951">During the audited period, the amount of expenditure related to the upgrade of the EMCS system in the Slovak Republic per shipment is 2.3 times higher than the expenditure of the same type in the Czech Republic.</seg>
<seg id="952">Conclusion</seg>
<seg id="953">The cooperation between the SAO of the Czech Republic and the SAO of the Slovak Republic has achieved its objectives.</seg>
<seg id="954">Both audit institutions gained a deeper knowledge of the system of administration of excise duties in the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic.</seg>
<seg id="955">It was found that, despite the common basic legal framework, there are significant differences between the two tax systems which affect the efficiency of excise administration.</seg>
<seg id="956">Parallel checks have identified examples of good practice that could contribute to reducing tax fraud, which will become increasingly important as tax rates rise.</seg>
<seg id="957">Procedures to reduce the costs of administering excise duties have also been identified.</seg>
<seg id="958">Mutual cooperation has revealed differences that significantly affect the efficiency of tax administration and limit international comparisons unless coordinated due diligence is carried out with the tax administration.</seg>
<seg id="959">In this, the role of supreme audit institutions is indispensable.</seg>
