<seg id="1">Report on the results of a parallel audit of the VAT administration carried out in the Czech Republic and the Federal Republic of Germany</seg>
<seg id="2">Introductory word</seg>
<seg id="3">The 1977 Lima Declaration stresses that the Supreme Audit Institutions (SAIs) have the power to audit all public financial operations.</seg>
<seg id="4">The declaration calls for tax revenues to be controlled as far as possible.</seg>
<seg id="5">The European Organisation of Supreme Audit Institutions (EUROSAI) considers taxes to be one of the most important components of public revenue.</seg>
<seg id="6">The VI. EUROSAI Congress held in Bonn in 2005 dealt with the audit of public revenue carried out by the SAI.</seg>
<seg id="7">The development of a specific strategy for the audit of public revenue is an important step towards optimising SAI control activities.</seg>
<seg id="8">This applies in particular to taxation as the bulkiest source of public revenue, which is the most vulnerable to large losses.</seg>
<seg id="9">As national economies become increasingly interconnected and dependent, SAIs may to some extent be unable to carry out control activities without the cooperation of another state's SAI.</seg>
<seg id="10">An example is the audit of internationally organised fraud, which causes significant income losses in many countries.</seg>
<seg id="11">In order to combat this crime, the responsible authorities need to work together.</seg>
<seg id="12">The Sai, which carry out checks in this area, must be willing to cooperate more closely with each other.</seg>
<seg id="13">It was at the VI EUROSAI Congress in Bonn that the idea arose to carry out an audit of the administration of value added tax ("VAT") and the VIES system in the framework of cooperation between the Supreme Audit Office and the Federal Court of Auditors, the Bundesrechnungshof.</seg>
<seg id="14">This was followed by careful preparation, where both parties first had to familiarise themselves with the legal environment and procedures for administering VAT in the Czech Republic and the Federal Republic of Germany.</seg>
<seg id="15">On the basis of an analysis of this information, a selection of control topics was carried out and included in the control programme.</seg>
<seg id="16">Achieving an efficient and efficient VAT administration has been a long-standing challenge and individual states (especially European Union Member States) are looking for solutions to improve, simplify and make the collection of VAT more transparent.</seg>
<seg id="17">We believe that the results of our inspection can serve not only to improve the work of tax authorities, but also as a basis for a proposal to improve the system of international exchange of information.</seg>
<seg id="18">Report on the results of parallel checks on the administration of value added tax carried out in the Czech Republic and the Federal Republic of Germany</seg>
<seg id="19">Introduction</seg>
<seg id="20">Control number: (CZ) 06 / 27 (D) VIII 2 - 2005 - 1215</seg>
<seg id="21">Subject of inspection:</seg>
<seg id="22">(CZ) Administration of value added tax after the accession of the Czech Republic to the European Union</seg>
<seg id="23">(D) Examination of administrative cooperation in the field of value added tax pursuant to Council Regulation (EC) No 1798 / 2003 and Commission Regulation (EC) No 1925 / 2004</seg>
<seg id="24">Objective of the inspection:</seg>
<seg id="25">(CZ) The aim of the audit operation in the Czech Republic was to examine the procedure of the tax authorities in the administration of value added tax following the integration of the Czech Republic into the single internal market of the European Union ("EU") linked to the free movement of goods and services and to examine the use of the VIES system, in particular when checking the application of the right to exemption from value added tax for intra-Community supplies.</seg>
<seg id="26">(D) The aim of the audit was to examine the system for the control of intra-community value added tax, with a particular focus on administrative cooperation in the field of value added tax under the aforementioned regulations.</seg>
